>{{cite news|title=Seek ups stake in JobStreet|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/technology/seek-ups-stake-in-jobstreet/story-e6frgakx-1225839201938|accessdate=7 March 2014|newspaper=The Australian|date=10 March 2010}}</ref> SEEK Limited, the Australian internet job recruitment company made a complete takeover in 2014 for RM 1.73 billion <ref>{{cite news|title=Australia's SeekAsia buying JobStreet's business for RM1.73b (Update)|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2014/02/19/Seek-Ltd-to-acquire-online-ops-of-Jobstreet-for-RM1dot73bil/|accessdate=7 March 2014|newspaper=The Star|date=Feb 19, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=JobStreet to pay almost all of $661 million from sale of online business as dividend |url=http://business.asiaone.com/news/jobstreet-pay-almost-all-661-million-sale-online-business-dividend|accessdate=7 March 2014|newspaper=Asia News Network|date=Feb 20, 2014}}</ref> together with co-investors, [[News Corp (2013\u2013present)|News Corp]], Tiger Global and [[Macquarie Capital]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Moullakis|first=Joyce|title=Behind the deal: SEEK\u2019s Asia push a long game|url=http://www.brw.com.au/p/business/behind_the_deal_seek_asia_push_long_oUukBIrXh3G5NH2DAANc1O|accessdate=7 March 2014|newspaper=BRW|date=24 Feb 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align: center; font-size:95%; width:99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n! Reference\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2015\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Asia Recruitment Awards - Malaysia\n|Best Career Website\n|Gold\n|<ref name=\"2015MYasiarecruitmentawards\">{{cite journal|title=Winners announced: Asia Recruitment Awards Malaysia|url=http://www.humanresourcesonline.net/asia-recruitment-awards/2015/my/2015/05/13/winners-announced-asia-recruitment-awards-malaysia/|work=Human Resources|accessdate=June 7, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Recruitment Innovation\n|Gold\n|<ref name=\"2015MYasiarecruitmentawards\"/>\n|-\n|Asia Recruitment Awards - Singapore\n|Best Career Websi